author: Lawrence O. Hall and Nitesh V. Chawla and Kevin W. Bowyer
title: Combining Decision Trees Learned in Parallel

window: The Iris data (Fisher 1936; Merz & Murphy ) which has 4 continuous valued attributes and classifies 150 examples as one of 3 classes of Iris plant. The second is the Pima Indians Diabetes data set (Merz & Murphy ) which has 8 numeric attributes and classifies 768 examples into one of 2 classes.
